</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Power off the system</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">On the operator panel, tap on the [System] icon on the right. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Tap on [Power management]. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Tap on [Power off]. The system shuts down. 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3" valign="top"/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Switch off the power supply</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the system has shut down, pull to open the cover under the roll winder. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Switch the power switch to the 'off' position. 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3" valign="top"/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Unplug the mains cables. 
